channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Students Sue AOC, Other 'Squad' Members Over Their Support for Violent Pro-Hamas Columbia U Protests
Kari Lake to hold 'Democrats for Lake' event after Democrats tout Republican support for Harris, Gallego
item.description: Republican Arizona Senate candidate Kari Lake on Tuesday called on the media to cover an upcoming event that will include current and former Democrats supporting her campaign.

item.title: Harris Wins Democrat Presidential Nomination in Virtual Roll Call
item.description: Democrat delegates have selected Vice President Kamala Harris to be the party's presidential nominee, according to final vote results released late Monday by the Democratic National Committee.Harris claimed the nomination after a five-day online voting process, receiving...

item.title: Jamie Raskin Appears to Say Congress Will Disqualify Trump If He Wins the Election, Threatens Civil War
Kamala Harris holding rally in Pennsylvania to introduce running mate after securing Democratic nomination
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris will hold a rally Tuesday in Pennsylvania to reveal her running mate. This is her first visit to Pennsylvania as the Democratic presidential nominee.

item.title: AIPAC Targets Squad Member Over Infrastructure Vote
item.description: Rep. Cori Bush, D-Mo., has faced a barrage of advertising from AIPAC, a pro-Israel lobbying group, ahead of her tough primary.

item.title: The New York Times Is Concerned That Kamala Harris Is Not Dressing Presidential Enough
Key primaries in 4 states on Tuesday to set table for November Senate, House showdowns
item.description: Key Republican and Democrat nomination contests on Tuesday as Michigan, Missouri, Kansas and Washington state hold primary elections on Tuesday.

item.title: Rep. Steil to Newsmax: Dems' ActBlue Probed for Possible Fraud
item.description: Rep. Bryan Steil, R-Wis., told Newsmax on Monday that stronger regulations to ensure compliance with campaign finance laws are needed.

item.title: WATCH: After Markets Tank, Trump Wastes No Time in Blasting Harris for The 'Kamala Crash' in Brutal Ad
What is GARM? 'Collusive' ad group allegedly targeting conservatives faces grilling from top House committee
item.description: GARM claims to be an apolitical group that assists companies with advertising while some Republicans claim it has a more sinister goal.

item.title: NM Governor Targets Texas Docs with Abortion Rights Ads
item.description: New Mexico Democrat Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham is trying to lure medical professionals from Texas to practice in her state with a $400,000 ad campaign - "Free to Provide," according to NM Health.

item.title: NYC Sanitation Dept. Saves Day With Much-Needed Humor After RFK Jr.'s Bizarro Bear Cub Dumping Story
It's official: Vice President Kamala Harris formally wins the Democratic presidential nomination
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris is now formally the Democratic Party's 2024 presidential nominee, following the conclusion of a virtual roll call.

item.title: Sen. Wyden: Thomas Didn't Disclose More Private Jet Travel
item.description: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas failed to disclose an additional two flights he took on Republican donor Harlan Crow's private jet, Sen. Ron Wyden, D-Ore., chair of the Senate Finance Committee, said Monday.
